n the range $10-100pM_\\odot$ (where\n$1pM_\\odot=10^{-12}M_\\odot$). The corresponding ionization rate due to SLRs\ntypically falls in the range $\\zeta_{SLR}\\sim1-5\\times10^{-19}$ sec$^{-1}$.\nThis ionization rate is smaller than that due to cosmic rays,\n$\\zeta_{CR}\\sim10^{-17}$ sec$^{-1}$, but will be important in regions where\ncosmic rays are attenuated (e.g., disk mid-planes).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 20 May 2014 16:12:27 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-19"}
